      "text": [
        ": قُلْتُ لَهُ رَجُلٌ تَزَوَّجَ بِجَارِيَةٍ عَاتِقٍ عَلَى أَنْ لاَ يَقْتَضَّهَا ثُمَّ أَذِنَتْ لَهُ بَعْدَ ذَلِكَ قَالَ \"إِذَا أَذِنَتْ لَهُ فَلاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4612 - It is narrated from Ishaq in Ammar, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdullah (as): A man married a young bondwoman with the condition that he would not deflower her. Then afterward, she gave him permission.\nImam (as) replied: \"If she gave him permission, then there is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
